            "type": "text",
            "text": "Approval Policies"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "An approval policy is a declarative rule \u2014 or set of rules \u2014 that determines whether a given action requires human review, can be auto-approved, or must be blocked outright. Policies separate the question of what needs approval from the mechanism that enforces it. Getting this separation right lets you adjust risk posture across environments and roles without changing agent code."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Approval policy layered decision stack and evaluation flow",
          "title": null
