            "text": "Summary"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Approval policies give you a single declarative location to control what requires human oversight. Define rules as predicate-decision pairs, order them with explicit priorities, and ensure DENY rules always take precedence. Load environment-specific overrides at startup to separate dev/staging/prod behaviour without if-else chains in agent code. Test every rule in isolation \u2014 policies that aren't tested will drift from the intent they were written to capture."
          }
